						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Tribhuvanachchakkravartigaḷ Śrī Vīrarājēndrachōḷa Year 34: <hi rend="italic">Mēsha</hi>, śu. di. 5 <hi rend="italic">Mrigaśirsba</hi>, Wednesday = March 30, 1278 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> by Kaliyugamēyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Nandipaṉmaṉ, one of the <hi rend="italic">agambaḍmudali</hi> of Sōḻagaṅgadēva in order to burn a twilight lamp to the deity Nīrvaṇṇaperumāḷ at Tirunīrmalai in Śurattūr-nāḍu of Kulōttuṅgasōḻa-vaḷanāḍu in Puliyūr-kōṭṭam (a sub-division) of Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḻa-maṇḍalam. Naimiśai Kauśika Bhaṭṭaṉ, the priest of the temple had received the gift and agreed to burn the lamp perpetually.</p>						

						</summary>
